RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHURCHILL DOWNS RACE 1 5F Dirt CR: 85. Maiden Special Weight Purse 92000. FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 119 lbs. (For Horses That Sold Or RNA For $50,000 Or Less In Their Most Recent Auction).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FROSTY THE GIANT pressed the leader from the outside entering the turn, bid nearing the lane, led in upper stretch, and drove clear at the furlong grounds. WEST SARATOGA chased along the inside, vacated the rail in upper stretch before bidding for place along with an outer rival at the sixteenth pole, and held that position from that one thereafter. PATCH O'BRIEN chased from the three path, then stayed on in the four path to bid for place entering the sixteenth pole along with an inner foe, but was for place denied by that rival late. FIVE STAR RUN lacked speed in the two path around turn, improved inside of rivals in upper stretch, and ran on. DUNPHY set the pace along the inside, but was headed by the eventual winner in upper stretch, and weakened on his left lead. FIVE O' SOMEWHERE broke slowly, gained midpack position along the inside entering the turn, shifted out entering the lane, but lacked a bid. INNOCENT MAN took mild bumps from an outer rival at the start, laid off of the pace in the four to five path, and failed to factor. IMPERIAL THUNDER bumped an inner rival at the start, pursued from off of the pace in the five to six path, and made little impact. MIDNIGHT STORMY broke slowly and never got involved from the five path. NUEVO AMANECER steadied soon after the start when an outer rival took his path, then saved ground far back to no avail. NOBLE GENTLEMAN broke a step slow, and was outrun in the three to four path.

ENTRY.COMMENT: chased inside, place bid btwn 1/16, dueled, held

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CLOSING ACT broke a step slowly, tracked two wide and between horses around the turn, tipped to the five path in upper stretch, then sustained a grinding charge to bid in the closing stages and edged ahead. FOOLISH FRONT FIFI brushed with an outer rival in the early stages, chased along the inside, rallied with good energy three wide and between horses entering the final sixteenth, sparred with an outer rival late, but got outfinished. KRICKLE pressed outside of the top pair, sustained a chase to bid along with rivals on either side in the final sixteenth, but was outkicked by them. TOO FAST FOR YOU set the pace along the inside, maintained a clear margin through midstretch, but was overhauled in the final sixteenth. APRIL CLOVER prompted the pace two wide, chased the clear leader in upper stretch, and gave way in the final furlong. YOU'RE KITTEN ME backed out from between horses entering the lane, and failed to factor two wide. GIRLS WEEKEND veered outwardly while off very slow, was urged along in the four path around the turn, and tired in the six path in upper stretch. BELLA VALENTINA brushed with an inner rival early on, and was outrun along the inside.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: TELL ME WHEN set the pace along the inside, and held well from outer chasers through the lane. MOON MAGIC CHRISSY laid closer up along the inside while pulling under stout restraint leading the chute, steadied along from the eleven sixteenths pole to the nine sixteenths pole, stalked along the inside around the turn, tipped to the three path to take aim outside of the leader entering the lane, but failed to progress on that one through the final furlong, and held place late. GHOSTLY GIRL tracked two wide and between horses, but retreated to trail passing the three furlong pole, tipped three wide turning for home, rallied inside of foes in upper stretch before shifting out at the furlong grounds, and stayed on but did not have enough to gain place. FRIGID LADY laid off of the pace four wide, spun into the lane in the six path, and lacked a bid. MEAN SUE tracked three wide, came into the lane in the five path while between horses and weakened. CHARLEE MAE pressed two wide, but weakened between horses turning for home.

Claiming Price $100,000 (Races Where Entered For $62,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances). (If deemed inadvisable by manag ement to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One and One Eighth mile.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TIBERIUS MERCURIUS vied for the lead two wide, led narrowly in hand around the far turn, then sparred with his inner counterpart through the lane via a long battle, and won the nod at the wire. HARLAN ESTATE set the pace inside of a vying rival, was roused while headed around the far turn, gamely prolonged the war through the lane, but narrowly lost the head bob at the wire. VINTAGE PRINT tracked three wide, chased outside of the embattled leading pair around the far turn, then failed to gain through the lane and held show. DASH ATTACK pursued from off of the pace two wide and between horses, tipped four wide in upper stretch, and offered a mild kick. VIVAR laid off of the pace three wide and between horses, eased back to trail leaving the nine sixteenths pole, swung out six wide approaching midstretch, and stayed on. FOUNDER saved ground towards the rear, but to no avail. TOMMY BEE stalked along the inside, chased under urging around the far turn, and weakened. FENWICK STATION got a bit crowded between horses soon after the start, settled off of the pace while hung four wide around both turns, then tired between horses after being floated five wide in upper stretch.

COUSIN LARRY laid off of the pace two wide and between horses, and failed to factor. SPIN WHEEL was slow into stride and made little impact. MASTER GAME was taken in hand after a step slow at the start, laid off of the pace along the inside and faded.
